## New Project: disprove
- **Replaces:** BurntSushi/quickcheck (43.8M downloads, 52 major dependents, 2.7k stars, abandoned 5+ years)
- **Why:** Foundational property-based testing crate for Rust. Last release v1.0.3 (~Feb 2021). Single maintainer no longer active. No maintained drop-in fork (qcheck: 0 stars). proptest has different API (strategy-based vs trait-based) and is itself only in passive maintenance. Known bugs unfixed. Missing modern Rust features.
- **Crate:** disprove (verified available on crates.io)
- **Features:** Arbitrary trait + impls for all std types, Gen random generator, shrink iterators, QuickCheck test runner, #[quickcheck] proc macro, quickcheck-compatible API
- **Improvements:** const generics arrays, async support, better shrinking performance, no_std, Rust 2024 edition, deterministic seeds
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #763 (scaffolding), #764 (core Arbitrary + Gen), #765 (collection/std Arbitrary impls), #766 (test runner), #767 (proc macro + compat)

